data.title: Why Camp Rock is better than your Summer Camp
data.meta_description: Back when Demi Lovato and the Jonas Brothers ruled the Disney Channel, Camp Rock was the hit TV movie of the year. Check out why Summer camp at Camp Rock was better than your average camp!
data.text:
In June 2008, Disney Channel released Camp Rock just in time to get the kids pumped up for summer! The DCOM starred the then-rulers of Disney Channel, Demi Lovato and the Jonas Brothers. Yes, all three Jonas Brothers, Nick, Joe and Kevin. Mitchie Torres (Demi Lovato) is an aspiring singer-songwriter who is a little shy, but has always dreamed of going to Camp Rock. Mitchie’s family can’t afford to send her to the prestigious music camp, so her mom (played by Wizards of Waverly Place’s Maria Canals Barrera) takes a job at the summer camp as their caterer, but in order to attend the camp with her mom, Mitchie must help out in the kitchen. Enter Shane Gray, played by Joe Jonas. Shane is an already famous front man for a musical group of brothers called Connect 3 (can you guess who the other two members are?). He’s let fame get to his head and is not excited to be an instructor at the camp he was sent to in order to get rid of his attitude. All caught up? So what exactly makes this camp better than your average summer camp? Well, you’re about to find out.

Joe Jonas teaches your classes

Yeah, he really does. He teaches campers all about being a performer, including a hip hop dance class which includes some microphone handling. It really is kind of cute, but not very good. Horribly entertaining to watch, though.

You get to hear ‘Connect 3’ perform what is probably one of my favorite Jonas songs ever.

You have Demi Lovato as a BFF…

You get to dance with Alyson Stoner.

Advertisement

The Jonas Brothers are around, literally all the time.

You get to look at Joe Jonas’ atrocious hair EVERY.DAY. You’re welcome.

You don’t have to deal with the summer heat too much…

Advertisement

Needless to say, we can all agree that Camp Rock is every Demi/Jonas fangirl’s dream camp. I mean, where do I sign up? I don’t mind Joe’s bad hair days all that much.
